First Read: 13-Jan-26
SB94 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to disabled parking; to amend Sections
5 32-6-231, 40-12-300, and Section 32-6-233.1, as last amended
6 by Act 2025-399 of the 2025 Regular Session, Code of Alabama
7 1975, to further provide for the unauthorized use of
8 designated disability parking places; to require certain
9 individuals to notify the Department of Revenue of the death
10 of a disabled individual who was issued a windshield placard;
11 and to authorize the Department of Revenue to create an
12 electronic scanning system for disability placards.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. Section 32-6-233.1, Code of Alabama 1975, as
15 last amended by Act 2025-399 of the 2025 Regular Session, and
16 pursuant to that act is effective until October 1, 2028, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 "§32-6-233.1
19 (a)(1) It shall be unlawful for any person individual
20 who does not have a distinctive special long-term access or
21 long-term disability access license plate or placard or
22 temporary disability placard as provided in Section 32-6-231,
23 or who is not transporting a passenger who has a distinctive
24 special long-term access or long-term disability access
25 license plate or placard or temporary disability placard as
26 provided in Section 32-6-231, to park a motor vehicle in a
27 parking place designated for individuals with disabilities at
28 any place of public accommodation, at any business or legal
Page 1

any place of public accommodation, at any business or legal
SB94 Enrolled
29 entity engaged in interstate commerce or which is subject to
30 any federal or state laws requiring access by individuals with
31 disabilities, at any amusement facility or resort, or at any
32 other place to which the general public is invited or
33 solicited, even though located on private property., unless
34 the individual meets one of the following requirements:
35 a. The individual is the lawful holder of a distinctive
36 special long-term access or long-term disability access
37 license plate or placard or a temporary disability placard.
38 b. The individual is transporting a passenger who is a
39 lawful holder of a distinctive special long-term access or
40 long-term disability access license plate or placard or a
41 temporary disability placard.
42 (2) Upon conviction, notwithstanding any other penalty
43 provision that may be authorized or employed, the person
44 individual shall be fined a minimum of fifty dollars ($50) for
45 the first offense, a minimum of two hundred dollars ($200) for
46 the second offense, and a minimum of five hundred dollars
47 ($500) for the third or any subsequent offense. In addition,
48 for the second or any subsequent offense under this section
49 subdivision (1), the person individual shall be ordered by the
50 court to perform a minimum of 40 hours of either of the
51 following forms of community service:
52 (1)a. Community service for a nonprofit organization
53 that serves individuals with disabilities or serves
54 individuals who have a disabling disease.
55 (2)b. Any other community service that may sensitize
56 the individuals individual to the needs and obstacles faced
