57 daily by individuals with disabilities.
58 (b) Any authorized municipal, county, or state law
59 enforcement officer may go on private property to enforce this
60 section.
61 (c) This section may be enforced by any law enforcement
62 officer who has successfully complied with the minimum
63 standards for police officers as set forth in Section
64 36-21-46, including, but not limited to, municipal law
65 enforcement officers, sheriffs, deputy sheriffs, and Alabama
66 State Troopers. Any law enforcement officer enforcing this
67 section may ask for verification that either the driver or a
68 passenger of the parked vehicle is the lawful holder of a
69 distinctive special long-term access or long-term disability
70 access license plate or placard or temporary disability
71 placard.
72 (d) Any sign designating a special access parking or
73 disability access parking place may contain on the sign or
74 attached to the sign the amount of the fine for a parking
75 violation on the first offense pursuant to subsection (a).
76 (e)(1) If the law enforcement officer who issues the
77 special access parking or disability access parking violation
78 is employed by a local law enforcement agency, 100 percent of
79 the fines collected pursuant to this section shall be paid to
80 the municipal or county general fund for the use of the law
81 enforcement agency by whom the arresting officer is employed.
82 (2) If the law enforcement officer who issues the
83 special access parking or disability access parking violation
84 is employed by a state law enforcement agency, the fines
