92 Program for individuals with developmental disabilities.
93 (3) All funds deposited to a separate fund in the State
94 Treasury pursuant to this subsection to be expended by the
95 Department of Mental Health, the Administrative Office of
96 Courts, and state law enforcement agencies shall be
97 appropriated by the Legislature, for the purposes stated in
98 this subsection. The expenditure of such sums so appropriated
99 shall be budgeted and allotted pursuant to the Budget
100 Management Act and Article 4 of Chapter 4 of Title 41. No
101 monies deposited to this fund shall revert to the State
102 General Fund at the end of any fiscal year. Prior to the
103 release of any monies to the Individual and Family Support
104 Program, such expenditures shall first be approved by the
105 Commissioner of the Department of Mental Health.
106 (f) This section shall be held in pari materia with all
107 other provisions of law related to illegal special access
108 parking or disability access parking violations and all laws
109 or parts of laws which conflict with this section are
110 repealed.
